Man WC is so boring! How about a little fight(or run) but just rarely and totally random.   :D 
[code=java]	// a random event(fighting)
	if (DataConversions.random(0, 100) == 0) {
		int lvl = owner.getCombatLevel();
		int npcId = 1;
		if (lvl <= 11) {
			npcId = 21; // mugger
		}
		else if (lvl >= 12 && lvl <= 33) {
			npcId = 74; // giant spider
		}
		else if (lvl >= 34 && lvl <= 65) {
			npcId = 104; // moss giant
		}
		else {
			npcId = 216; // tree spirit(set agresive on NPCDEF.xml)
		}
		final Npc foe = new Npc( npcId, owner.getX(), owner.getY(), owner.getX() - 5, owner.getX() + 5, owner.getY() - 5, owner.getY() + 5);
		foe.setRespawn(false);
		world.registerNpc(foe);
		Instance.getDelayedEventHandler().add(new SingleEvent(null, 60000) {
			public void action() {
				Mob opponent = foe.getOpponent();
				if (opponent != null) {
					opponent.resetCombat(CombatState.ERROR);
				}
				foe.resetCombat(CombatState.ERROR);
				world.unregisterNpc(foe);
				foe.remove();
			}
		});
	}[/code]

As you can see, it only misses some general dialogue(or scream) from the monsters and when the back-flip animation get released the moss giant will perform a stealth attack instead of standing on the tree branches.  :o
